T1  - Quotas versus tariffs
AU  - Pelcovits, Michael D.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 6
IS  - 4
SP  - 363
EP  - 370
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/11/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(76)90036-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199676900362
AB  - This paper examines the nonequivalence of tariffs and quotas under uncertainty, when the expected level of imports is constrained for noneconomic reasons. Tariffs and quotas are ranked according to their effect on expected social welfare. In the case of a stochastic foreign supply curve, the ranking will depend upon the height of the tariff. In the case of a stochastic import demand curve, a tariff will always yield greater social welfare than a quota.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Trade, growth and consumption in alternative models of capital accumulation
AU  - Smith, M.A.M.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 6
IS  - 4
SP  - 371
EP  - 384
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/11/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(76)90037-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199676900374
AB  - This paper shows that some of the most interesting effects of international trade on capital accumulation are essentially the same in a range of different technologies: input-output models, vintage models, and the standard two-sector model. Trade and autarky equilibria are compared on the assumption that the rate of profit is the same in both cases. The effect of trade on intertemporal choice is analysed, with emphasis on the case where steady state consumption falls as a result of trade. Alternative saving assumptions are discussed.
ER  - 
